%N A108940 Values of c associated with A108287.
%C A108940 From _Andrew Howroyd_, Mar 14 2023, in A108287: (Start)
%C A108940 The following information was extracted from the Derive script and notes.
%C A108940 The values of x and y are not required to be integers or even real numbers.
%C A108940 Eliminating x and y from the equations gives: a^3 - 3*a*b + 2*c = 0.
%C A108940 This is the Diophantine equation that is being solved. For a given b and c there will be three possibly complex roots. It is required to find those values of b and c where all three roots are integers.
%C A108940 The values for b are the integers of the form (d^2 + d*e + e^2)/3 where d and e are positive integers and d <= e. This sequence lists these values in order with repetition.
%C A108940 The corresponding values for c are d*e*(d+e)/2 given in A108940, and the three values for a are d, e and -(d+e). (End)
%H A108940 David Cleaver, <a href="/A108940/b108940.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a>
